Description: Part of a jar-seal: of pale brown clay, now in three fragments, with remains of a seal-impression of Khasekhem. The surface of the clay is considerably worn.
Curator's comments: Bibliography: W. M. F. Petrie, 'Royal Tombs of the Earliest Dynasties' II, pl.XXIII, 193; P. Kaplony, 'Die Inschriften der Ägyptischen Frühzeit III (Wiesbaden, 1964), pl.82, abb.310; see also vols. I, 161 and II, 854, n.977; 1135.
